  <brief_title>Clinical Trial to Slow the Progression of ADPKD</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK)</agency>
      <agency_class>NIH</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will determine whether certain blood pressure medications will slow cyst growth
      or keep kidneys functioning longer in patients with autosomal dominant polycystic kidney
      disease (ADPKD). The study will take place at several sites in the United States. The start
      date of the study has not yet been determined.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
